Columns.Name: ShopperAbsolutePositionX
Columns.Description: An absolute (raw) measurement of the shoppers position based on the  X-Axis.

Columns.Name: ShopperAbsolutePositionY
Columns.Description: An absolute (raw) measurement of the shoppers position based on the  Y-Axis.

Columns.Name: ShopperAbsolutePositionZ

Columns.Name: ShopperAbsolutePositionUom

Columns.Name: ShopperPositionRotationX
Columns.Description:
Rotation X is the amount of rotation (in degrees) relative to the X axis of the Store Floor.  The rotation point is the center of the object which is aligned with the Floor Location X,Y coordinate.

Rotation angle is usually defined according to the right-hand rule. Namely, the angle is a positive value when the rotation appears clockwise when looking in the positive direction of the axis, and negative values when the rotation appears counter-clockwise.

Columns.Name: ShopperPositionRotationY
Columns.Description:
Rotation Y is the amount of rotation (in degrees) relative to the Y axis of the object.  The Y axis refers to vertical position (perpendicular to the base).  A positive rotation would mean that the front of the object's base plane is higher than the back, whereas a negative value indicates the front of the object's base plane is lower than the back.  

A shopper position that is angled downward would be a negative Rotation Y value, whereas a shopper position that is angled upward would be a positive Rotation Y value.

Columns.Name: ShopperPositionRotationZ
Columns.Description: Rotation Z is the amount of rotation (in degrees) relative to the Z axis of the object.  The Z axis refers to the rotational axis or rotational centerline of the object.  A positive rotation would mean that one side of the object's base plane is higher than the other,  whereas a negative value indicates the opposite side is higher.  In other words, it is leaning to the left or to the right.

Columns.Name: FloorLocationXCoordinate
Columns.Description: The floor location x-coordinate of the shopper position.

Columns.Name: FloorLocationYCoordinate
Columns.Description: The floor location y-coordinate of the shopper position.

Columns.Name: FloorLocationZCoordinate
Columns.Description: The floor location z-coordinate of the shopper position.

Columns.Name: ShopperPositionTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Shopper Position Type.

Properties.Description: Shopper Position indicates where a shopper is located within the store layout, as well as the orientation of the shopper or position types that are part of the shopper.
